frameDefinitions: A Driver prepares a Vehicle for travel by placing it in the normal location for the operation of the vehicle or by detaching it from a place where it was held.
These words refer to separating a Whole into Parts, or separating one part from another.
A Perceiver determines the Location of a Sought_entity within a Ground.
A Figure is (stably) located with respect to a Ground in terms of how the distance between them compares to some general or contextually relevant scale.
An Inspector attains a degree of certainty in the Unconfirmed_content, generally by inspecting some evidence.
A Whole separates into Parts, or one part of a whole, called Part_1, becomes separate from the remaining portion, Part_2.
